# Purpose: Optimize Ollama model temperature & context window for local coding
# Note: this model used for planning [in Cline]

# HOW TO: 
# 1) cd to directory where Modelfile is located
# 2) ollama create cline-planner -f .\Modelfile_plan -f Modelfile_plan
# 3) Verify parameters of new model: ollama show --parameters cline-planner

# Base model
FROM llama3.2

# Set temperature to 0.0 for maximum precision; higher = more creative
PARAMETER temperature 0.1

# CPU cores - set to 'performance' core count
PARAMETER num_thread 8

# Set a large context window for Cline to see your whole project (should correspond to max RAM on system to avoid memory swapping)
PARAMETER num_ctx 65536

# Top P (Nucleus Sampling): Limits the token pool to a cumulative probability. 
# Lowering this from the default (0.9) to 0.8 ensures the model only considers the most logical next steps.
PARAMETER top_p 0.8

# Top K: Hard caps the token selection to the 20 most likely tokens (default is 40). 
# This prevents the model from "derailing" or hallucinating during long planning phases.
PARAMETER top_k 20

# Min P: Filters out extreme long-tail (nonsense) tokens to keep the plan focused.
PARAMETER min_p 0.05

# Repeat Penalty: Prevents the model from getting stuck in infinite loops 
# when generating repetitive file structures, boilerplate, or long lists.
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.15